#MEM id=session-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/shared/skills/operating-system/session-protocol/SKILL.md savings=19%
M||tx|---
M||name|sn-protocol
M||desc|Universal sn start and end protocol for all yv ag. Defines file load order, memory write obligations, ADJOURNING checklist, and self-improvement logging. Every ag runs this — no exceptions.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||appl|all-ag
M||tx|---
M|Sess|tx|> This is the shared standard. ag-specific sn notes live in each ag's `MEMORY.md`.
M|Sess|> So|`shared/skills/operating-sy/sn-protocol/SKILL.md`
M|Sess|tx|---
M|Sess|tx|```
M|Sess|tx|1. Read this ag's MEMORY.md                ← permanent patterns, Never Again rules
M|Sess|tx|2. Read doc/os/sn.md                     ← global in-flight state
M|Sess|tx|3. Read doc/memory/feedback.md               ← 🔴 ct ds/routing rules
M|Sess|tx|4. Check Last Clean Exit timestamp in sn.md
M|Sess|→ If|flag abrupt exit before proceeding
M|Sess|5. I|load doc/vt/[active]/sn.md
M|Sess|6. I|load doc/vt/[active]/ds.md
M|Sess|7. I|load doc/vt/[active]/FEEDBACK.md
M|Sess|tx|```
M|Sess|tx|**Never load all files at once. Load only what the current task requires.**
M|Sess|tx|---
M|Sess|tx|```
M|Sess|1. B|npx tsc --noEmit → MUST pass before ADJOURNING
M|Sess|2. A|
M|Sess|tx|[date] — [task] — [outcome] — [what I'd do differently]
M|Sess|tx|3. Append one row to doc/os/sn.md (global log, no duplicates)
M|Sess|4. I|append to doc/vt/[active]/sn.md
M|Sess|5. P|
M|Sess|tx|{ agentId, vt, summary, learnings[], corrections[], filesChanged[], toolCallsCount }
M|Sess|6. W|YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM" to doc/os/sn.md
M|Sess|tx|```
M|Sess|tx|---
M|Self|Afte|
M|Self|1. E|**what went wrong → rule that prevents it**
M|Self|2. C|
M|Self|it|vt-specific → `doc/vt/[name]/FEEDBACK.md`
M|Self|it|ag-specific → this ag's `MEMORY.md` Never Again section
M|Self|it|Universal → `doc/memory/feedback.md`
M|Self|tx|3. **Never save the same rule in two places** (Memory Sync Rule from WORKFLOW.md)
M|Self|4. I|the rule MUST already exist — if it doesn't, add it now
M|Self|tx|---
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|tx|[YYYY-MM-DD] [vt-tag or universal] — task — outcome — rule going forward
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|Exam|
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|[202|always segment hb churn by acquisition cohort, never flat average
M|Memo|[202|triple-pass before any delivery, no exceptions even for "simple" changes
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|tx|---
M|Erro|When|
M|Erro|tx|1. Log the er pattern to `MEMORY.md` Never Again section
M|Erro|tx|2. Note the fix that resolved it
M|Erro|tx|3. Flag to qn for `er-log-audit` if it was a production rt er
M|Erro|tx|---
M|Anti|it|Starting work before checking sn.md for in-flight context
M|Anti|it|Ending a sn w/o writing to MEMORY.md (even "No gap found" is a valid entry)
M|Anti|it|Writing the same rule to multiple files (pick one location, per Memory Sync Rule)
M|Anti|it|Skipping the bd check and going straight to ADJOURNING on broken code